#:proof{:extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :proved, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :classification :proved, :reclassification-reason "Post-hoc: zero sorry with substantive declarations", :output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (A,B closed in ℝ, f:ℝ→[0,1]) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (conclusion only after hypotheses) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (encodes entire separation statement) · notes: helper lemma ensures denominator positivity.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:problem-id 't94A02\n :frame-id 'apm-v2-t94A02-1775009748581\n :goal \"Construct a continuous function f : ℝ → [0,1] that separates two disjoint closed subsets A and B by sending A to 0 and B to 1.\"\n :terms [{:name \"disjoint closed subsets\"\n          :meaning \"Closed sets A,B ⊆ ℝ with A ∩ B = ∅\"\n          :needed-because \"Their closedness lets us use distances; disjointness keeps the denominator positive.\"}\n         {:name \"distance to a set\"\n          :meaning \"d(x,A) = inf_{a∈A} |x−a|\"\n          :needed-because \"This function is continuous and vanishes exactly on A (similarly for B).\"}\n         {:name \"normalization\"\n          :meaning \"h(x)=d(x,A)/(d(x,A)+d(x,B)) maps into [0,1] and hits the desired fibers.\"\n          :needed-because \"Ensures f^{-1}(0)=A and f^{-1}(1)=B by algebraic manipulation.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"metric.distance_set, continuous_iinf, normalization algebra\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Define d_A(x)=dist(x,A) and d_B(x)=dist(x,B). They are continuous, nonnegative, and vanish exactly on A resp. B. Since A and B are disjoint closed, d_A+d_B>0 everywhere. Set f=d_A/(d_A+d_B). Then f(A)=0, f(B)=1, and f takes values in [0,1].\"\n             :why-this-now \"This is the classical Urysohn-style construction specialized to ℝ with its metric; explicit distance formulas are available.\"\n             :lean-target \"ApmCanaries.Frames.T94A02.Apm_v2_t94A02_1775009748581.separate_closed_sets\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib has continuity of distance-to-set and related lemmas; the normalization step should already exist.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done\n                :stage2 :done\n                :stage3 :in-progress\n                :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:problem-id 't94A02\n :main-claim {:informal-claim \"Given disjoint closed A,B ⊆ ℝ, there is a continuous f:ℝ→[0,1] with f^{-1}(0)=A and f^{-1}(1)=B.\"\n             :formal-name \"separate_closed_sets\"\n             :formal-target \"∀ (A B : Set ℝ), IsClosed A → IsClosed B → Disjoint A B →\n  ∃ f : ℝ → ℝ, Continuous f ∧ f '' Set.univ ⊆ Set.Icc 0 1 ∧ f ⁻¹' {0} = A ∧ f ⁻¹' {1} = B\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"Encodes exactly the separation statement requested.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"separate_closed_sets\"\n               :formal-statement \"∀ (A B : Set ℝ), IsClosed A → IsClosed B → Disjoint A B →\n  ∃ f : ℝ → ℝ, Continuous f ∧ f '' Set.univ ⊆ Set.Icc 0 1 ∧ f ⁻¹' {0} = A ∧ f ⁻¹' {1} = B\"\n               :informal-clause \"Certifies the full statement from Stage 1.\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"distance_partition\"\n               :formal-statement \"∀ x, dist (x,A) + dist (x,B) > 0\"\n               :informal-clause \"Shows the denominator used in the normalization is positive (thanks to disjointness).\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n- Built the full reader-facing write-up in `.../execute.md`, covering the difficulty analysis, key insight, full proof, dependency graph, Lean plan, and Stage 4 reflections so the frame record now has real content.\n- Updated the machine-readable artifacts—`proof-plan.edn` (Stage status